+## Data Flow
+
+### End-to-End: Opening an Issue
+
+```
+User clicks "Issues" in sidebar
+  │
+  ├─ TanStack Router navigates to /issues/:owner/:repo
+  ├─ Route loader calls client-side action
+  │   └─ WebSocket request to server: { method: "issues.listIssues", params: { owner, repo } }
+  │
+  ▼
+Server WebSocket route
+  ├─ Calls IssuesService.listIssues(input)
+  │   └─ Effect flows through GitHubClient.request()
+  │       └─ GitHubClient wraps Octokit response in Effect
+  │           └─ Mapper converts snake_case → camelCase
+  │
+  ├─ If error: classifyGitHubError → typed Error → response with error tag
+  ├─ If success: response with data
+  └─ Push result back over WebSocket
+      │
+      ▼
+React client receives response
+  ├─ Updates local store / cache
+  └─ Renders IssueList with IssueView cards
+```
+
+### End-to-End: Code Review Agent Executes on PR
+
+```
+PR is created (or user triggers review manually)
+  │
+  ├─ Webhook / user action → server routes to AgentOrchestrator
+  │
+  ▼
+AgentOrchestrator
+  ├─ Calls "agent:before_run" hook (notifies plugins)
+  ├─ Looks up "code-review" agent from AgentRegistry
+  ├─ Builds ReviewContext:
+  │   ├─ repo, prNumber, title, description
+  │   ├─ PullRequestsService.listPullRequestFiles() → FileChange[]
+  │   ├─ ReviewsService.listReviews() → existingComments
+  │   └─ branches
+  │
+  ├─ Calls AgentRegistry.dispatch("code-review", reviewContext)
+  │   └─ CodeReviewAgent.execute(context)
+  │       └─ Returns ReviewOutput { summary, comments, ... }
+  │
+  ├─ Submits review via ReviewsService.createReview()
+  ├─ Calls "agent:after_run" hook (notifies plugins)
+  └─ Returns result to caller
+```
+
+### Plugin Hook Firing Sequence
+
+```
+Event occurs (e.g., issue created)
+  │
+  ├─ Core service fires hook: hookEmitter.emit("issue:created", context)
+  │
+  ├─ HookEmitter sorts handlers by priority (descending)
+  ├─ For each handler:
+  │   ├─ Await handler(context)
+  │   ├─ If handler throws → log error, continue to next handler
+  │   └─ Continue
+  │
+  └─ All handlers complete → control returns to caller
+```
