+## Extension / Open Library Model
+
+### How Third Parties Contribute Providers
+
+Any plugin can contribute a new Git provider by providing a `ProviderContribution` in its manifest. The OmniCode core handles resolution:
+
+1. **Plugin declares** `contributes.providers` with provider metadata (type, baseUrl, auth method)
+2. **Plugin's agent** (or the plugin's `activate()` function) registers the provider implementation with the `SourceControlProviderRegistry` (from T3 Code)
+3. **Core's ProviderDispatcher** includes plugin-provided providers when matching remote URLs
+4. **UI automatically** renders provider-specific terminology (PR vs MR, etc.) via `ChangeRequestPresentation`
+
+#### Adding a New Provider (Example: Gitea)
+
+```typescript
+// my-gitea-plugin/src/index.ts
+import { OmniCodePlugin, type PluginContext } from "@omnicode/plugin";
+
+class GiteaProvider implements SourceControlProviderShape {
+  // Implement all required methods using Gitea's REST API
+}
+
+export default {
+  id: "gitea-provider",
+  activate(context: PluginContext) {
+    // Register with T3 Code's SourceControlProviderRegistry
+    // (hook available via context injection)
+    context.log("info", "Gitea provider activated");
+  },
+} satisfies OmniCodePlugin;
+```
+
+With manifest:
+
+```json
+{
+  "name": "gitea-provider",
+  "omnicode": {
+    "id": "gitea-provider",
+    "main": "dist/index.js",
+    "contributes": {
+      "providers": [{
+        "id": "gitea",
+        "name": "Gitea",
+        "type": "gitea",
+        "baseUrl": "https://gitea.com",
+        "authType": "token",
+        "capabilities": ["listPRs", "listIssues", "searchRepos"]
+      }]
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+### How Third Parties Contribute Agents
+
+Agents contributed by plugins go through the same lifecycle as built-in agents:
+
+1. **Plugin declares** `contributes.agents` in manifest
+2. **Plugin's `activate()`** registers agent instances with the `AgentRegistry`
+3. **Agent Registry** makes them discoverable via `getAgents()` and dispatchable via `dispatch()`
+4. **Agent Orchestrator** can invoke them on matching events
+
+### Plugin Registration Workflow
+
+```
+Plugin Development
+  ├─ Write OmniCodePlugin class
+  ├─ Define manifest in package.json
+  └─ Build → publish (npm, local directory, or Git repo)
+
+Installation
+  └─ User places plugin in configured pluginDirs (configurable in OmniCodeConfig)
+
+Activation
+  ├─ Server starts → PluginLoader discovers plugins
+  ├─ PluginRegistry.loadAll(dirs)
+  │   ├─ discoverPlugins → validate manifests
+  │   └─ For each: loadModule → validate → activate()
+  └─ Plugin.activate(context) → register hooks, contributions, agents
+
+Runtime
+  ├─ Hooks fire → plugin handlers execute
+  ├─ UI renders contributed routes and paints
+  └─ Agent registry dispatches plugin agents
+
+Deactivation
+  ├─ Plugin deactivated → deactivate() called
+  ├─ HookEmitter.clear(pluginId) → removes all handlers
+  └─ PluginState → "inactive"
+```
+
